<br>
Its a Kunark era weapon, and the mere fact that up until SoL was still a very powerful pet shows that it was grossly overpowered in both Kunark and Velious.  Its time has passed, and while it may still tank better than the new pets, thanks to its innate DS, stuns, and procs, its a relic of the past, and there is no viable excuse for making it lvl 60 or 55 or anything higher than what it was.  Some classes still use their epics, I know... Ive heard it all ... Rangers use Swiftwind, clerics use the click stick, Shamen use the Spear, Monks use the Fists, blah blah.  I see lots of rangers using Vyhzdra's Render of Souls in their offhand, or other comparable weapons... Monks use the Fists because the haste effect is a song and allows them to carry another Haste item simultaneously ... in other words, Monks use the Fists out of convenience.  Shamen use the Spear out of convenience... mana-free DoT, but the DoT is not amazing by any measure compared to Luclin/PoP spells.  Clerics will always use their Click-Stick for its useful purpose, but many clerics switch it out with weapons that have better stats/effects.<br>
<br>
